      • path

        public <S extends Pathable & Strictable & Unstricable & Customable & InstanceBuilderFirst & FillerFirst & Metric<S> & Using<S>> S path(String path)
        Description copied from interface: Pathable
        Creates selector builder based on paths. Fields, indexes of collection elements or arrays can be used. 
             public class TestClass {
         private String myField;
         ...
     }

     Dsl dsl = new DashaDsl()
          .defs();                        // create default rules for object creation.

     dsl.strict(TestClass.class)     // matche only TestClass.class
        .path("myField")                // matche fiedls with name "myField"
        .simple(ctx -> "My value");     // create instance builder with fixed generated value: "My values"
        Specified by:
        path in interface Pathable
        Type Parameters:
        S - type of selector builder.
        Parameters:
        path - path.
        Returns:
        selector builder.

      • path

        public <S extends Pathable & InstanceBuilderFirst & FillerFirst & Metric<S> & Using<S>> S path(GetMethodReference reference)
        Description copied from interface: Pathable
        Creates selector builder based on path described by method parameters. Next two calls are equivalent: 
             public class TestClass {
          private String myField;

          public String getMyField() {
              return this.myField;
          }
          ...
     }

     Dsl dsl = new DashaDsl()
          .defs();                                    // create default rules for object creation.

          dsl.path(TestClass::getMyField);            // (1) first form.
          dsl.path("myField").strict(String.class);   // (2) second form are equivalent to (1) first one.
        Specified by:
        path in interface Pathable
        Type Parameters:
        S - type of selector builder.
        Parameters:
        reference - method reference.
        Returns:
        selector builder.

      • strict

        public <T,S extends Pathable & Customable & InstanceBuilderFirst<T> & FillerFirst<T> & Metric<S> & Using<S>> S strict(Type type,
                                                                                                                      Type... genericTypeArgs)
        Description copied from interface: Strictable
        Method returns object for building selector chain with class check element. The selector that will be created uses the Object.equals(Object) method to test the context. 
              Dsl dsl = new DashaDsl()
          .defs()                                     // create default rules for object creation.
          .strict(String.class)                       // matche only String.class
          .simple(ctx -> "This is a test string");    // create instance builder with fixed generated value: "This is a test string"
